> Think you know pineapple? Think again. You haven't truly experienced it until it's been warmed through and caramelized to bring out all of its juicy sweetness. And when you toss it into a taco with some gently spiced pieces of tilapia and a crispy slaw, everything you think is true about the fruit is suddenly flipped on its head as you venture into savory dinnertime territory.

Adjust rack to top position and heat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees.

Wash and dry all produce. Drain @pineapple{8%ounce}, then place in a #medium bowl{}. Chop half the @cilantro{1/4%ounce} (save the rest for garnish). Halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges. Halve and peel @shallot{1}; mince until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mince @garlic{2%clove} until you have ½ tsp (1 tsp for 4).

To #bowl{} with pineapple, add minced shallot, half the chopped cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice; stir to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @tilapia{11%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, then season all over with salt, pepper, and @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. Rub seasoning into tilapia to thoroughly coat. Broil or bake on top rack until lightly charred and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of garlic. (TIP: Add garlic to taste, or leave it out if you're not a fan.) Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

In a second medium bowl, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, remaining chopped cilantro, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings), a squeeze of lime juice, and 1 TBSP crema (2 TBSP for 4); toss to thoroughly combine. Season with salt, pepper, and more lime juice to taste. Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Once cool enough to handle, break up tilapia into bite-size pieces. Divide between tortillas along with slaw and salsa. Drizzle with remaining crema. Tear leaves from reserved cilantro and sprinkle over tacos. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.